  <theorem xml:id="lecture-notes-thm-sum-of-squares-formula">
    <title>Sum of Squares Formula</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        For any real numbers <m>a</m> and <m>b</m>, it is always true that
        <me>a^2+b^2=(a+bi)(a-bi)</me>.
        In other words, the sum of squares is the product of a complex number and its complex conjugate.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </theorem>

